Class FileHandler

java.lang.Object
FileHandler
public class FileHandler
extends java.lang.Object
This FileHandler class handles your files by performing following operations.

1) Display files in ascending order.

2) Operations

2.1)Add File / Folder.

2.2)Delete File.

2.3)Search for a file.

At first it requires a valid path of folder/directory on which you want to perform operations. Make sure the path is not system secure. It will repetitively ask for a path till Path is not valid or Folder is not present.

    • MainMenu

      public static void MainMenu() throws java.io.IOException, java.util.InputMismatchException
      This Method is for Displaying Main Menu where user have 4 options

      1 )To Display Files in ascending order.

      2 )Perform various operations on File.

      3 )To change the current folder.

      4 )to exit the Program.

      java.io.IOException - For Invalid Input
      java.util.InputMismatchException - For alphabetic input.

    • operationMenu

      public static void operationMenu() throws java.io.IOException, java.util.InputMismatchException
      This Function display Operation Menu where user would have following three operations to perform on a File.

      1 )To Add a File/Folder.

      2 )To Remove a File/Folder.

      3 )Search For a File.

      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - If User give invalid Input or the File which does not exists.
      java.util.InputMismatchException

    • addFileOrDir

      public static void addFileOrDir() throws java.io.IOException, java.util.InputMismatchException
      When user choose option 1 from Operation Menu, this method is executed. In this Menu User have 2 option

      1 )To make new File.

      2 )To make new Folder.

      Throws:
      java.io.IOException -

      1 )For invalid Path or Invalid Input.

      2 )If the Access to path is denied due to security reasons.

      java.util.InputMismatchException

    • addFile

      public static boolean addFile()
      To create a new File. User have to give input as File name which he wants to create.

      The Method is Case-Sensitive.

      If the Folder/File (with same extension) with given input is already present in folder, file would not be created and it will return False on unsuccessful.
      Returns:
      Return True if the File is created SuccessFully else False.

    • addFolder

      public static boolean addFolder()
      To create a new Folder. User have to give input as Folder name which he wants to create.

      The Method is Case-Sensitive.

      If the Folder/File (without extension) with same name is already present in folder, folder would not be created and it will return False on unsuccessful.
      Returns:
      True if the Folder is created SuccessFully else False.

    • deleteFile

      public static void deleteFile() throws java.io.IOException
      To Delete the user specified File/Folder. It will again ask for confirmation of Deleting the File/Folder by displaying the details of same.

      The Method is Case-Sensitive.

      Throws:
      java.io.IOException -

      1 )If the specified File/Folder is not Present

      2 )The Folder Have some security issues.

      3) the specified Folder is not Empty.

      4)Access is Denied.

    • searchFile

      public static void searchFile() throws java.io.IOException
      For Searching the user specified File/Folder in the current Folder/Directory. If the File is present, it will print the path of file with file name.

      If the searched path is folder, it asks user whether he want to change his current directory to searched one.

      The Method is Case-Sensitive.

      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - For Invalid Input From User

    • displayFiles

      public static void displayFiles() throws java.io.IOException
      Displays The Files in Current Folder in ascending order with respect to name of Files.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - For Invalid Input
